[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has a nice 2\C opening hand.

With 8 points, NORTH can make a positive response so he bids his 5-card \Hsuit.

SOUTH likes \Hs, knows there are at least 33 points, but needs to make 
sure the opponents don't have two Aces so she uses Blackwood.

When NORTH shows one Ace SOUTH bids 6\H.}

